Package com.natwest.opendata.service.products

Class PCAServiceImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.natwest.opendata.service.products.PCAServiceImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseOpenDataService<PersonalCurrentAccounts>, PCAService
    public class PCAServiceImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements PCAService
    The PCAServiceImpl class is an implementation of PCAService Interface. All methods pertaining to PCA functionalities are implemented in this class.

    PCAServiceImpl is public class, an implementation, that get exposed to the developers or consumer of this SDK. Because PCAServiceImpl is public class, its methods are visible and can be consumed.

    Here are some more examples of how PCAService can be used: 

         Recommended way to use:
     OpenDataService openDataService=new OpenDataService(Environment.PROD);
      PCAService pcaService=openDataService.getPCAService();
      pcaService.getAllData();

    The class PCAServiceImpl includes methods for consuming various functionalities pertaining to PCAs open data SDK, for example getting all PCAs data as list, filtering PCAs based on properties such as PCAMarketingState, FeeCategory and FeeType.

    Exposed Methods:

    • getPCAByFilter
    • getPCAByPCAMarketingState
    • getPCAByFeeCategory

      • getPCAByFilter

        public java.util.List<PersonalCurrentAccounts> getPCAByFilter​(@NonNull
                                                              @NonNull PCAFilterEnum filterName,
                                                              @NonNull
                                                              @NonNull java.lang.String filterValue)
        Filters PersonalCurrentAccounts response based on the attributes present in the PersonalCurrentAccounts response. filterName specified as the first parameter is the property in PersonalCurrentAccounts response and filterValue specified as the second parameter is the value of that property, against which the filtering is required This method returns filtered list.

        The Items in a list or array is seperated by ; instead of , to avoid conflict in csv file

        Specified by:
        getPCAByFilter in interface PCAService
        Parameters:
        filterName - Takes Enum PCAFilterEnum which has various filtering criteria
        filterValue - Takes string, which maps to the property value in PersonalCurrentAccounts service response
        Returns:
        filtered list of PersonalCurrentAccounts on which criteria are applied.
